description.narrative: Government at national and subnational levels has improved capacity to implement intersectoral policies for social protection with emphasis on the most vulnerable children., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Education â€“ General, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Social Protection And Child Poverty, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021 boys and girls have increased access to quality and responsive health, education and social protection programmes, and actively participate in the design, implementation and monitoring of these services.

description.narrative: 2,023 municipalities got enrolled in 2021-2024 UNICEF Municipal Seal Programme and 7,500 public servants from these municipalities participated in the trainings to implement public policies to fulfil children’s rights. This means that 86 per cent of the municipalities from Semiarid and Amazonian regions accepted UNICEF invitation to develop a set of seven systemic results in a participatory process that includes adolescents and youth engagement and mobilization. Nine national organizations, including the consortium of Governors of Amazônia and consortium of Governors from the Northeast have been supporting municipalities in the implementation of public policies of education, health, and social assistance. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2022
